checkAccountApproveDenyOracles((uint32,b.details: This function receives an array of rule ids, which it uses to get the oracle details, then calls the oracle to determine permissions.

checkTokenMaxBuyVolume(uint32,uint256,ui.details: Function receives a rule id, retrieves the rule data and checks if the Token Max Buy Volume Rule passes

params.amountToTransfer: total number of tokens to be transferred in transaction.
params.boughtInPeriod: total amount of tokens purchased in current period
params.currentTotalSupply: total supply value passed in by the handler. This is for ERC20 tokens with a fixed total supply.
params.lastPurchaseTime: time of the most recent purchase from AMM. This starts the check if current transaction is within a purchase window.
params.ruleId: id of the rule to be checked

checkTokenMaxSellVolume(uint32,uint256,u.details: Function receives a rule id, retrieves the rule data and checks if the Token Max Sell Volume Rule passes

params.amountToTransfer: total number of tokens to be transferred in transaction.
params.currentTotalSupply: total supply value passed in by the handler. This is for ERC20 tokens with a fixed total supply.
params.lastSellTime: time of the most recent purchase from AMM. This starts the check if current transaction is within a purchase window.
params.ruleId: id of the rule to be checked
params.soldWithinPeriod: total amount of tokens sold within current period

checkTokenMaxSupplyVolatility(uint32,int.details: Rule checks if the Token Max Supply Volatility rule will be violated.

params._lastSupplyUpdateTime: the last timestamp the supply was updated
params._tokenTotalSupply: the total supply from token tallies
params._volumeTotalForPeriod: token's trading volume for the period

returns._0: _volumeTotalForPeriod properly adjusted total for the current period
returns._1: _tokenTotalSupply properly adjusted token total supply. This is necessary because if the token's total supply is used it skews results within the period

checkTokenMaxTradingVolume(uint32,uint25.details: Rule checks if the Token Max Trading Volume rule will be violated.

params._amount: Number of tokens to be transferred from this account
params._lastTransferTime: the time of the last transfer

checkTokenMinTxSize(uint32,uint256).details: Check if transaction passes Token Min Tx Size rule.

params.amountToTransfer: total number of tokens to be transferred

returns._0: tokenMaxSupplyVolatility Rules total length of array
